page.title: 01Dartford_West Thurrock
page.content: This is a predominately industrial area of North Kent/South Essex and includes an expanse of the Thames estuary with associated marsh land. Included in the area are the towns of Dartford,West Thurrock,Purfleet,and Swanscombe. Major industries include cement making paper making,quarrying(chalk),and oil refining. Other major features are: 1)Central Electricity Generating Board power station complex at Littlebrook, near Dartford 2)Dartford tunnels and M25 London orbital motorway. 3)'Crossways 25' a major industial and distribution centre,including roll_on roll_off container port,in the process of development on a site adjacent to the Dartford tunnels.
